<subSubSection type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="39" pageNumber="40">The identity of this characteristic species is certain. Berlese (1887a) recorded it from North Italy; in the Collection I studied only a specimen from Vallombrosa (no. 39/20).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageId="39" pageNumber="40">According to Jacot (1936) and Strenzke (1952) the species mainly occurs in litter and moss in coniferous forests.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
